# Scope for issue #12 D2: the guard dimension.
#
# D1 shipped the format, the V9 binding, and the CLI. D2 adds exactly one
# thing — the PreToolUse check — so the diff should stay inside the guard
# command. If it reaches internal/, the design drifted: this check is
# deliberately built out of pieces D1 already provides (contract.InScope,
# snapshot.GetActiveContract) rather than new library surface.
name: contracts-d2
description: #12 D2 — the edit-scope guard dimension (RUNECHO_GUARD_CONTRACT)

cmd/runecho-guard/contract.go
cmd/runecho-guard/contract_test.go

# The wiring points. A new hook check cannot exist without touching the hook
# and the record it logs, so these are in scope by necessity, not by drift —
# and naming them is the point: the reviewer sees exactly which shared files
# this work was allowed to reach, and any OTHER file in cmd/runecho-guard/
# still asks.
cmd/runecho-guard/main.go
cmd/runecho-guard/declog.go

# The contract declares its own file, otherwise every check reports itself.
# CHANGELOG.md is deliberately absent: release automation writes it from commit
# subjects, so a hand-edit here would be drift, not documentation. The flag
# itself is documented where every other experimental flag is — the package doc
# in cmd/runecho-guard/main.go.
.runecho/contracts/**
